His wife says he is lazy and won't fix a thing: the house is falling apart. Harry had kept a jug of battery water on a rickety shelf, and it was hit by lightning. When he gets back home the shelves have broken, the jug has spilled, and the house is flying higher and higher. Both fame and the house are out of reach.
